- Knapsack
|-Here an item taken as a whole or not taken at all
|-selection of items based on value/weight ratio
|-sometimes greedy fails to give optimal solution

- Fractional Knapsack
|-Items can be broken into smaller pieces
|-selection of items based on value/weight ratio
|-always gives optimal solution

- Activity Selection
|-Sort activities by finish time
|-If its start time is greater than or equal to the finish time of the last selected activity, select it.
|-Update the last selected activity to the current one

- Job Sequencing
|-Sort jobs by profit in descending order
|-Find Maximum deadline among all jobs
|-create a slot array of size max_deadline+1 and initialize it with -1
|-For each job, find a free slot from its deadline to 1 , any slot that is free and less than or equal to the deadline will be assigned to the job
|-If a free slot is found, assign the job to that slot and mark it as occupied
|-Print the selected jobs and their total profit

- Dijkstra's Algorithm
|-Single source shortest path algorithm for graphs with non-negative edge weights
